2 Verum sciendum est idem et de aliis delictis dici posse. Nam illis quoque puniendis Deus haud dubie sufficit, et tamen ea ab hominibus recte puniuntur, nemine dissenti- ente. Instabunt quidam et dicent, alia delicta ab hominibus puniri, quatenus homines alii inde laeduntur aut periclitantur. Sed notandum contra, non tantum ab hominibus puniri delicta quae directe alios laedant, sed et quae per consequentiam, qua- lis sui occisio, concubitus cum bestiis, et alia quaedam.

2 But it is to be recollected that this may be said of other offensos also. For God is no doubt sufficient to punish these also; and yet they are rightly punished by men, no one dissenting. Some pursue the argument, and say, that other offenses are punishcd by men, so far as men are by them hurt or injured. But it is to be noted, on the other hand, that offenses arc punished which not only hurt others directly, but those also which do so by consequence, as sels-murder, and bestiality, and others.
